    <stitle>POWER STEERING GEAR: TRW/ROSS-TAS 40, 55, 65 AND 85 - INSPECT</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl0500313" svcproctype="inspect" graphiccount="7">
        <title>INSPECT</title>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>Any of the following conditions present in the steering gear indicates impact damage. If one of
                    these conditions is found in one component, be sure to inspect all components carefully for signs of
                    impact damage. Replace components noted in individual inspection steps below if you suspect impact
                    damage. Failure to replace all damaged components could result in a serious vehicle accident.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <table id="hl0500314">
            <title>Impact Damage</title>
            <tgroup cols="2">
                <colspec colname="1" colwidth="2.44in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" colwidth="3.68in"/>
                <spanspec namest="1" nameend="2" spanname="s1t2"/>
                <tbody>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>Condition</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Area</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>Brinelling</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Ball track grooves of rack piston</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Ball track grooves of worm screw</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Bearing area of sector shaft</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Thrust washers and bearings in valve housing</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>Cracks or Breaks</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Bearing area of sector shaft</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Sector shaft teeth</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Rack piston teeth</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Housing</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Thrust washers and bearings in valve housing</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Worm screw</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>Twisted Serrations</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Output shaft serrations</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="s1t2">
                            <para>If one of these conditions is found in one component, be sure to inspect all
                                components carefully for signs of impact damage. Replace components noted in individual
                                inspection steps below if you suspect impact damage. Failure to replace all damaged
                                components could result in a serious vehicle accident.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Make sure all sealing surfaces and seal cavities are free from nicks and corrosion. Any
                nicked or corroded surface requires part replacement to ensure proper sealing.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the rack piston (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0500350">Figure 50</hotlnk>) teeth for cracks or obvious damage. If teeth are damaged,
                replace the rack piston, sector shaft and set of balls.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0500350" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0500350" filename="../figg05/G0500350.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="192px"
                         scalefitheight="152px"/>
                <caption>Figure 50. Inspect Rack Piston</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the rack piston ball track grooves for brinelling or spalling (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0500351">Figure 51</hotlnk>). If either condition exists, replace the input shaft,
                valve/worm assembly, valve housing, rack piston subassembly and balls.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0500351" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0500351" filename="../figg05/G0500351.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="192px"
                         scalefitheight="152px"/>
                <caption>Figure 51. Inspect Ball Track Grooves</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the sealing area of input shaft and valve for nicks and damage. Inspect for
                discoloration from excess heat. Inspect input shaft ball-track grooves for brinelling or spalling. If
                any of these conditions exist, replace the input shaft, valve worm assembly, valve housing and balls.
                Also replace rack piston if brinelling or spalling is found (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0500352">Figure 52</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0500352" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0500352" filename="../figg05/G0500352.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="192px"
                         scalefitheight="152px"/>
                <caption>Figure 52. Inspect Sealing Area</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the housing cylinder bore. Some scoring marks are normal. If there was internal
                leakage greater than 1 gal/min, make sure there are no damaged seals before replacing the housing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0500353">Figure 53</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0500353" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0500353" filename="../figg05/G0500353.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="192px"
                         scalefitheight="152px"/>
                <caption>Figure 53. Inspect Housing Cylinder Bore</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the housing faces for nicks that would prevent proper sealing. Replace the gear
                housing if these nicks are present and cannot be easily removed with a fine-tooth flat file without
                changing the dimensional characteristics (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0500354">Figure 54</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0500354" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0500354" filename="../figg05/G0500354.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="192px"
                         scalefitheight="152px"/>
                <caption>Figure 54. Inspect Housing Faces</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">TAS40, 55, 65: Inspect side cover DU bushing for damage. Also check side cover bushing to
                sector shaft clearance. If damage exists, or if clearance exceeds .008 inch (0.20 mm), replace side
                cover/bushing assembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0500355">Figure 55</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <para>TAS85: Inspect roller bearing in side cover assembly for brinelling or spalling. If either condition
                exists, replace the side cover and bearing assembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0500355">Figure 55</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0500355" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0500355" filename="../figg05/G0500355.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="192px"
                         scalefitheight="152px"/>
                <caption>Figure 55. Inspect Side Cover</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the sector shaft bearing and sealing areas and sector teeth contact surfaces for
                brinelling, spalling or cracks. Run your fingernail edge across these areas to detect steps. Remove
                masking tape from the shaft and inspect for twisted or otherwise damaged serrations. If any of these
                conditions exist, replace the sector shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0500356">Figure 56</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0500356" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0500356" filename="../figg05/G0500356.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="192px"
                         scalefitheight="152px"/>
                <caption>Figure 56. Inspect Sector Shaft Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
